Sure, here are some free resources that you can use to learn Java:

1. [Oracle Java Tutorials](^3^): The official Java learning resource from Oracle³.
2. [Tutorialspoint](^3^): Java-specific programming courses are available through this interactive online learning platform³.
3. [Coursera](^3^): Offers a variety of Java courses³.
4. [YouTube Channels](^3^): There are numerous channels that offer free Java tutorials³.
5. [GitHub](^3^): You can find a lot of Java projects and tutorials³.
6. [Java Forums and Communities](^3^): These platforms can be very helpful for solving doubts and learning from others³.
7. [freeCodeCamp.org](^1^): Offers a comprehensive list of free Java courses for beginners¹.
8. [Codecademy](^2^): Provides a robust programming course to create software, web, and mobile apps².
9. [Udemy](^4^): While it offers both free and paid courses, you can find a good number of free Java courses⁴.

Remember, the best way to learn is by doing. So, try to practice as much as you can while learning. Happy coding! 😊

